        <description>&lt;img src="/post/coderunner/cover.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Code Runner" /&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;Intro&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CodeRunner.nvim is a versatile Neovim plugin designed to streamline the process of executing code directly within the Neovim environment. This document provides a comprehensive guide on installing, configuring, and contributing to CodeRunner.nvim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;lazynvim&#34;&gt;Lazy.nvim&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lua&#34; data-lang=&#34;lua&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;-- lazy.nvim setup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;use &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Coptan99/CodeRunner.nvim&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;packernvim&#34;&gt;Packer.nvim&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lua&#34; data-lang=&#34;lua&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;-- packer.nvim setup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;use &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Coptan99/CodeRunner.nvim&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;vim-plug&#34;&gt;vim-plug&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-vim&#34; data-lang=&#34;vim&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;#34; vim-plug setup&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Plug&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Coptan99/CodeRunner.nvim&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;supported-files&#34;&gt;Supported Files&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CodeRunner.nvim currently supports the following file types:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;Usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To execute the code in the active file, simply use the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-vim&#34; data-lang=&#34;vim&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;lua&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;require&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;coderunner&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;runner&lt;/span&gt;()&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;keymapping&#34;&gt;Keymapping&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For convenient access to the CodeRunner functionality, consider adding a key mapping to your Neovim configuration. Open your &lt;code&gt;init.vim&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;init.lua&lt;/code&gt; and append the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;example-keymapping&#34;&gt;Example Keymapping&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lua&#34; data-lang=&#34;lua&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;-- Example key mapping in init.lua&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;vim.keymap.set(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;lt;leader&amp;gt;qq&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;:lua require(&amp;#39;coderunner&amp;#39;).runner()&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Feel free to customize the key mapping according to your preferences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;configuration&#34;&gt;Configuration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CodeRunner.nvim is designed to be easily configurable. To tailor it to your specific needs, modify the key mapping in the provided configuration. Refer to the example key mapping above and adjust it accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;contribution&#34;&gt;Contribution&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contributions to CodeRunner.nvim are highly encouraged. If you have new ideas, enhancements, or bug fixes, feel free to submit a pull request. As the project evolves, your contributions play a crucial role in improving the functionality and user experience of CodeRunner.nvim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that all contributions should adhere to the project&amp;rsquo;s guidelines, and constructive feedback is always welcome. Whether you&amp;rsquo;re a seasoned developer or a beginner, your input is valued as we work together to enhance CodeRunner.nvim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thank you for considering CodeRunner.nvim, and happy coding!&lt;em&gt;CodeRunner.nvim Documentation&lt;/em&gt;*&lt;/p&gt;
